obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (23925)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23925&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the University Grants Commission`
  line `Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5th November, 1956, vide notification No. S.R.O. 2608, dated 1st November, 1956, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (23926)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23926&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Commission" means the University Grants Commission established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "executive authority", in relation to a University, means the chief executive authority of the`
  line `University (by whatever name called) in which the general administration of the University is vested;`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Fund of the University Grants Commission constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the University Grants Commission and includes the Chairman`
  line `^1[and Vice-Chairman];`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "University" means a University established or incorporated by or under a Central Act, a`
  line `Provincial Act or a State Act, and includes any such institution as may, in consultation with the`
  line `University concerned, be recognised by the Commission in accordance with the regulations made in`
  line `this behalf under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (23927)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Act to institutions for higher studies other than Universities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23927&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may, on the advice of the Commission, declare, by notification in the Official Gazette, that`
  line `any institution for higher education, other than a University, shall be deemed to be a University for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, and on such a declaration being made, all the provisions of this Act shall apply to`
  line `such institution as if it were a University within the meaning of clause (f) of section 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (23928)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23928&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Commission by the name`
  line `of the University Grants Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Commission shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal,`
  line `and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (23929)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for section 5 (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23929&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) The Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(i) a Chairman,`
  line
  line `(ii) a Vice-Chairman, and`
  line
  line `(iii) ten other members,`
  line
  line `to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman shall be chosen from among persons who are not officers of the Central`
  line `Government or of any State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Of the other members referred to in clause @/@(iii) of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) two shall be chosen from among the officers of the Central Government, to represent that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) not less than four shall be chosen from among persons who are, at the time when they are so`
  line `chosen, teachers of Universities; and`
  line
  line `(c) the remainder shall be chosen from among persons--`
  line
  line `(i) who have knowledge of, or experience in, agriculture, commerce, forestry or industry;`
  line
  line `(ii) who are members of the engineering, legal, medical or any other learned profession; or`
  line
  line `(iii) who are Vice-Chancellors of Universities or who, not being teachers of Universities, are,`
  line `in the opinion of the Central Government, educationists of repute or have obtained`
  line `high academic distinctions:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than one-half of the number chosen under this clause shall be from among`
  line `persons who are not officers of the Central Government or of any State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Vice-Chairman shall exercise such of the powers, and discharge such of the duties, of the`
  line `Chairman as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Every appointment under this section shall take effect from the date on which it is notified by the`
  line `Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (23930)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23930&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A person appointed as Chairman,`
  line `Vice-Chairman or other member after the commencement of the University Grants Commission`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1985 shall, unless he sooner becomes disqualified for continuing as such under the`
  line `rules that may be made under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of Chairman, hold office for a term of five years or until he attains the age of`
  line `sixty-five years, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of Vice-Chairman, hold office for a term of three years or until he attains the age`
  line `of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any other member, hold office for a term of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) a person who has held office as Chairman or Vice-Chairman shall be eligible for further`
  line `appointment as Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other member, and`
  line
  line `(ii) a person who has held office as any other member shall be eligible for further appointment as`
  line `Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person who has held office for two terms, in any capacity, whether as`
  line `Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other member [excluding a member referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5], shall not be eligible for any further appointment as Chairman,`
  line `Vice-Chairman or other member.]`
  line
  line `(2) A member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government,`
  line `but he shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairman, whether by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity, the Vice-Chairman`
  line `holding office as such for the time being shall, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5, act as the Chairman and shall, unless any other person is appointed earlier as the Chairman,`
  line `hold the office of the Chairman for the remainder of the term of office of the person in whose place he is`
  line `to so act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no Vice-Chairman is holding office at the time when the vacancy in the office`
  line `of the Chairman occurs, the Central Government shall, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 5, appoint any other member to act as the Chairman and the person so appointed`
  line `shall not hold the office of the Chairman for a period exceeding six months.`
  line
  line `(4) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Vice-Chairman or any other member, whether by`
  line `reason of his death, resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity,`
  line `such vacancy shall be filled up by the Central Government by making a fresh appointment and the`
  line `member so appointed shall hold office for a term of three years.`
  line
  line `(5) The office of the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman shall be whole-time and salaried and subject`
  line `thereto, the terms and conditions of service of the Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other members shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 70 of 1985, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 4, for sub-sections (3) and (4) (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (23931)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Meetings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23931&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be provided`
  line `by regulations made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (23932)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vacancies amongst members or defect in constitution not to invalidate acts or proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23932&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the Commission shall be deemed to be invalid by reason`
  line `merely of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (23933)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Temporary association of persons with the Commission for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23933&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commission may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined by`
  line `regulations made under this Act, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in carrying out any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the Commission under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a`
  line `right to take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting`
  line `of the Commission, and shall not be a member of any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (23934)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Staff of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23934&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in`
  line `this behalf, the Commission may appoint a Secretary and such other employees as it may think necessary`
  line `for the efficient performance of its functions under this Act and the terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `employees shall be such as may be determined by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (23935)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23935&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions`
  line `of the Commission shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other member`
  line `authorised by the Commission in this behalf, and all other instruments issued by the Commission shall be`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Secretary or any other officer of the Commission authorised in like`
  line `manner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (23936)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23936&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the general duty of the Commission to take, in`
  line `consultation with the Universities or other bodies concerned, all such steps as it may think fit for the`
  line `promotion and co-ordination of University education and for the determination and maintenance of`
  line `standards of teaching, examination and research in Universities, and for the purpose of performing its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Commission may--`
  line
  line `(a) inquire into the financial needs of Universities;`
  line
  line `(b) allocate and disburse, out of the Fund of the Commission, grants to Universities established or`
  line `incorporated by or under a Central Act for the maintenance and development of such Universities or`
  line `for any other general or specified purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) allocate and disburse, out of the Fund of the Commission, such grants to other Universities as`
  line `it may deem ^1[necessary or appropriate for the development of such Universities or for the`
  line `maintenance, or development, or both, of any specified activities of such Universities] or for any`
  line `other general or specified purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that in making any grant to any such University, the Commission shall give due`
  line `consideration to the development of the University concerned, its financial needs, the standard`
  line `attained by it and the national purposes which it may serve;`
  line
  line `^2[(cc) allocate and disburse out of the Fund of the Commission, such grants to institutions deemed`
  line `to be Universities in pursuance of a declaration made by the Central Government under section 3, as`
  line `it may deem necessary, for one or more of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) for maintenance in special cases,`
  line
  line `(ii) for development,`
  line
  line `(iii) for any other general or specified purpose;]`
  line
  line `^3[(ccc) establish, in accordance with the regulations made under this Act, institutions for`
  line `providing common facilities, services and programmes for a group of universities or for the`
  line `universities in general and maintain such institutions or provide for their maintenance by allocating`
  line `and disbursing out of the Fund of the Commission such grants as the Commission may deem`
  line necessary;]
  line
  line `(d) recommend to any University the measures necessary for the improvement of University`
  line `education and advise the University upon the action to be taken for the purpose of implementing such`
  line recommendation;
  line
  line `(e) advise the Central Government or any State Government on the allocation of any grants to`
  line `Universities for any general or specified purpose out of the Consolidated Fund of India or the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the State, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) advise any authority, if such advise is asked for, on the establishment of a new University or`
  line `on proposals connected with the expansion of the activities of any University;`
  line
  line `(g) advise the Central Government or any State Government or University on any question which`
  line `may be referred to the Commission by the Central Government or the State Government or the`
  line `University, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(h) collect information on all such matters relating to University education in India and other`
  line `countries as it thinks fit and make the same available to any University;`
  line
  line `(i) require a University to furnish it with such information as may be needed relating to the`
  line `financial position of the University or the studies in the various branches of learning undertaken in`
  line `that University, together with all the rules and regulations relating to the standards of teaching and`
  line `examination in that University respecting each of such branches of learning;`
  line
  line `(j) perform such other functions as may be prescribed or as may be deemed necessary by the`
  line `Commission for advancing the cause of higher education in India or as may be incidental or`
  line `conducive to the discharge of the above functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 5, for "necessary for the development of such Universities" (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 59 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (23937)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 13
  title `Regulation of fees and prohibition of donations in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 59 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23937&sectionno=12A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Regulation of fees and prohibition of donations in certain cases.--(1) In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "affiliation", together with its grammatical variations includes, in relation to a college,`
  line `recognition of such college by, association of such college with, and admission of such college to the`
  line `privileges of, a university;`
  line
  line `(b) "college" means any institution, whether known as such of by any other name which provides`
  line `for a course of study for obtaining any qualification from a university and which, in accordance with`
  line `the rules and regulations of such university, is recognised as competent to provide for such course of`
  line `study and present students undergoing such course of study for the examination for the award of such`
  line qualification;
  line
  line `(c) "prosecution", in relation to a course of study, includes promotion from one part or stage of`
  line `the course of study to another part or stage of the course of study;`
  line
  line `(d) "qualification" means a degree or any other qualification awarded by a university;`
  line
  line `(e) "regulations" means regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "specified course of study" means a course of study in respect of which regulations of the`
  line `nature mentioned in sub-section @I@(2) have been made;`
  line
  line `(g) "student" includes a person seeking admission as a student;`
  line
  line `(h) university means a university or institution referred to in sub-section (1) of section 22.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of section 12 if, having regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of any course of study for obtaining any qualification from any university;`
  line
  line `(b) the types of activities in which persons obtaining such qualification are likely to be engaged`
  line `on the basis of such qualification;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum standards which a person possessing such qualification should be able to`
  line `maintain in his work relating to such activities and the consequent need for ensuring, so far as may`
  line `be, that no candidate secures admission to such course of study by reason of economic power and`
  line `thereby prevents a more meritorious candidate from securing admission to such course of study; and`
  line
  line `(d) all other relevant factors,`
  line
  line `the Commission is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public interest, it may, after`
  line `consultation with the university or universities concerned, specify by regulations the matters in`
  line `respect of which fees may be charged, and the scale of fees in accordance with which fees shall be`
  line `charged in respect of those matters on and from such date as may be specified in the regulations in`
  line `this behalf, by any college providing for such course of study from, or in relation to, any student in`
  line `connection with his admission to, and prosecution of, such course of study:`
  line
  line `Provided that different matters and different scales of fees may be so specified in relation to`
  line `different universities or different classes of colleges or different areas.`
  line
  line `(3) Where regulations of the nature referred to in sub-section (2) have been made in relation to any`
  line `course of study, no college providing for such course of study shall--`
  line
  line `(a) levy or charge fees in respect of any matter other than a matter specified in such regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) levy or charge any fees in excess of the scale of fees specified in such regulations, or`
  line
  line `(c) accept, either directly or indirectly, any payment (otherwise than by way of fees) or any`
  line `donation or gift (whether in cash or kind),`
  line
  line `from, or in relation to, any student in connection with his admission to, and prosecution of, such course of`
  line study.
  line
  line `(4) If, after making, in relation to a college providing for a specified course of study, an inquiry in the`
  line `manner provided by regulations, and after giving such college a reasonable opportunity of being heard,`
  line `the Commission is satisfied that such college has contravened the provisions of sub-section (3), the`
  line `Commission may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, pass an order prohibiting such`
  line `college from presenting any students then undergoing such course of study therein to any university for`
  line `the award of the qualification concerned.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall forward a copy of the order made by it under sub-section (4) to the`
  line `university concerned, and on and from the date of receipt by the University of a copy of such order, the`
  line `affiliation of such college to such university shall, in so far as it relates to the course of study specified in`
  line `such order, stand terminated and on and from the date of termination of such affiliation and for a period of`
  line `three years thereafter affiliation shall not be granted to such college in relation to such or similar course of`
  line `study by that or any other university.`
  line
  line `(6) On the termination of the affiliation of any college under sub-section (5), the Commission shall`
  line `take all such steps as it may consider appropriate for safeguarding the interests of the students concerned.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section and the regulations made for the purposes of this section shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (23938)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 14
  title `Prohibition regarding giving of any grant to a University not declared by the Commission fit to receive such grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23938&sectionno=12B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[^212B.]Prohibition regarding giving of any grant to a University not declared by the Commission fit to receive such grant.--No grant shall be given by the Central Government, the`
  line `Commission, or any other organisation receiving any funds from the Central Government, to a University`
  line `which is established after the commencement of the University Grants Commission (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1972 (33 of 1972), unless the Commission has, after satisfying itself as to such matters as may be`
  line `prescribed, declared such University to be fit for receiving such grant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 6 (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Section 12A renumbered as section 12B of that section by Act 59 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984)`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (23939)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23939&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of ascertaining the financial needs of a University or its`
  line `standards of teaching, examination and research, the Commission may, after consultation with the`
  line `University, cause an inspection of any department or departments thereof to be made in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed and by such person or persons as it may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall communicate to the University the date on which any inspection under`
  line `sub-section (1) is to be made and the University shall be entitled to be associated with the inspection in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall communicate to the University its views in regard to the results of any such`
  line `inspection and may, after ascertaining the opinion of the University, recommend to the University the`
  line `action to be taken as a result of such inspection.`
  line
  line `(4) All communications to a University under this section shall be made to the executive authority`
  line `thereof and the executive authority of the University shall report to the Commission the action, if any,`
  line `which is proposed to be taken for the purpose of implementing any such recommendation as is referred to`
  line `in sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (23940)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Consequences of failure of Universities to comply with recommendations of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23940&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If any University ^1[grants affiliation in respect of any course of study to any college`
  line `referred to in sub-section (5) of section 12A in contravention of the provisions of that sub-section or] fails`
  line `within a reasonable time to comply with any recommendation made by the Commission under section 12`
  line `or section 13, ^2[or contravenes the provisions of any rule made under clause (f) or clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 25, or of any regulation made under clause (e) or clause (f) or clause (g) of`
  line `section 26,] the Commission, after taking into consideration the cause, if any, shown by the University`
  line `^3[for such failure or contravention,] may withhold from the University the grants proposed to be made out`
  line `of the Fund of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "for its failure to comply with such recommendation" (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (23941)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Payment to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23941&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission in each financial year such sums as may be`
  line `considered necessary for the performance of the functions of the Commission under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (23942)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Fund to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23942&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall have its own Fund; and all sums which`
  line `may, from time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government and all the receipts of the Commission`
  line `(including any sum which any State Government or any other authority or person may hand over to the`
  line `Commission) shall be carried to the Fund and all payments by the Commission shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may, subject to the approval of the Central Government, be decided by the Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act,`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (23943)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23943&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be`
  line `prescribed, a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated receipts and`
  line `expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (23944)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23944&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare once every year, in such form and at such time`
  line `as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous`
  line `year, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and the Government shall cause`
  line `the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (23945)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Account and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23945&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall cause to be maintained such books of account`
  line `and other books in relation to its account in such form and in such manner as may, in consultation with`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, as soon as may be after closing its annual accounts, prepare a statement of`
  line `accounts in such form, and forward the same to the Comptroller and Auditor-General by such date, as the`
  line `Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General, determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at such`
  line `times and in such manner as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The annual accounts of the Commission together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `to the Central Government and the Government shall cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line `Parliament and shall also forward a copy of the audit report to the Commission for taking suitable action`
  line `on the matters arising out of the audit report.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (23946)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Directions by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23946&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the`
  line `Commission shall be guided by such directions on questions of policy relating to national purposes as`
  line `may be given to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the Central Government and the Commission as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy relating to national purposes, the decision of the Central`
  line `Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (23947)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Returns and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23947&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall furnish to the Central Government such`
  line `returns or other information with respect to its property or activities as the Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (23948)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Right to confer degrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23948&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right of conferring or granting degrees shall be exercised only`
  line `by a University established or incorporated by or under a Central Act, a Provincial Act or a State Act or`
  line `an institution deemed to be a University under section 3 or an institution specially empowered by an Act`
  line `of Parliament to confer or grant degrees.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in sub-section (1), no person or authority shall confer, or grant, or hold himself`
  line `or itself out as entitled to confer or grant, any degree.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, "degree" means any such degree as may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, be specified in this behalf by the Commission by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (23949)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prohibition of the use of the word „University‟ in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23949&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No institution, whether a`
  line `corporate body or not, other than a University established or incorporated by or under a Central Act, a`
  line `Provincial Act or a State Act shall be entitled to have the word "University" associated with its name in`
  line `any manner whatsoever:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall, for a period of two years from the commencement of this`
  line `Act, apply to an institution which, immediately before such commencement, had the word "University"`
  line `associated with its name.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (23950)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23950&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 22 or section 23 shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and if the person contravening is an association or`
  line `other body of individuals, every member of such association or other body who knowingly or wilfully`
  line `authorises or permits the contravention shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (23951)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1984, s. 5, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23951&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for the retirement of members under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the disqualifications for continuing as a member of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of service of members of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms and conditions of service of employees appointed by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(e) the additional functions which may be performed by the Commission under clause (j) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) the returns and information which are to be furnished by Universities in respect of their`
  line `financial position or standards of teaching and examination maintained therein;`
  line
  line `(g) the inspection of Universities;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner in which the budget and reports are to be prepared by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which the accounts of the Commission are to be maintained;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner in which returns or other information are to be furnished by the`
  line `Commission to Central Government;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the rules or any of them but`
  line `no retrospective effect shall be given to any rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to`
  line `whom such rule may be applicable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (23952)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23952&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission ^1[may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make regulations] consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder,--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the meetings of the Commission and the procedure for conducting business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the manner in which and the purposes for which persons may be associated with`
  line `the Commission under section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) specifying the terms and conditions of service of the employees appointed by the`
  line Commission;
  line
  line `(d) specifying the institutions or class of institutions which may be recognised by the`
  line `Commission under clause (f) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(e) defining the qualifications that should ordinarily be required of any person to be appointed to`
  line `the teaching staff of the University, having regard to the branch of education in which he is expected`
  line `to give instruction;`
  line
  line `(f) defining the minimum standards of instruction for the grant of any degree by any University;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the maintenance of standards and the co-ordination of work or facilities in`
  line Universities.
  line
  line `^2[(h) regulating the establishment of institutions referred to in clause (ccc) of section 12 and other`
  line `matters relating to such institutions;`
  line
  line `(i) specifying the matters in respect of which fees may be charged, and scales of fees in`
  line `accordance with which fees may be charged, by a college under sub-section (2) of section 12A;`
  line
  line `(j) specifying the manner in which an inquiry may be conducted under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 12A.]`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation shall be made under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d)`
  line `^2[(orclause (h) or clause (i) or clause (j)]of sub-section (1) except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `^2[(3) The power to make regulations conferred by this section [except clause (i) and clause (j) of`
  line `sub-section (1)] shall include the power to give retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, to the regulations or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to`
  line `any regulation so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such regulation may be`
  line applicable.]
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "may make regulations" (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 59 of 1984, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (23953)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23953&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Power to delegate.--(1) The Commission may, ^2[`
  line `by regulations made, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette,] under this Act, delegate to its Chairman, Vice-Chairman or any of its officers, its power`
  line `of general superintendence and direction over the business transacted by, or in, the Commission,`
  line `including the powers with regard to the expenditure incurred in connection with the maintenance of the`
  line `office and internal administration of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation shall be made under this section except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1972, s. 8 (w.e.f. 17-6-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 1984, s. 7, for "by regulation made" (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (23954)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834&sectionId=23954&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00004_195603_1517807319834
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.-- Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is`
  line `in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session, or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.]`
